The paper deals with shape analysis and registration, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of quasi-conformal theory suggests that the paper may also fall under computational geometry (cs.CG) or complex analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of geometric morphometrics (cs.MM), which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the statistical analysis of biological shape variation.
